<DOCNO>GH950919-000049</DOCNO>
<DOCID>GH950919-000049</DOCID>
<DATE>950919</DATE>
<HEADLINE>Swinburn goes for Balanchine in Arc</HEADLINE>
<EDITION>3</EDITION>
<PAGE>32</PAGE>
<GRAPHIC>ILLUS</GRAPHIC>
<RECORDNO>976306339</RECORDNO>
<TEXT>
WALTER Swinburn has been booked to partner Oaks winner Balanchine,
while the other Godolphin runner, Derby winner Lammtarra, will have
champion jockey Frankie Dettori aboard in next month's Prix de l'Arc de
Triomphe at Longchamp.
The decision was announced by the syndicate's racing manager, Simon
Crisford, and caused an immediate reaction from one of the country's
leading bookmakers who tightened the odds of the Lammtarra to 4-1
favourite from 9-2 joint with his stablemate.
Balanchine, second behind Carnegie in last week's Prix Foy, is now a
5-1 chance for Europe's premier autumn event.
* MEDAILLE Militaire, 10-1 second favourite for the Cambridgeshire, is
set to run at Ascot instead. The colt has been declared for the
12-furlong Group 3 Cumberland Lodge Stakes, the opening event of the
two-day Festival of British Racing, on Saturday.
Trainer John Dunlop had issued a warning last week about the colt's
participation at Newmarket, and the Ascot entry confirms that the son of
Highest Honour will be aimed at races in excess of 10 furlogs.
Although he won one of the hottest mile handicaps of the year, the
Britannia at Royal Ascot, Michael Kinane reported that Medaille
Militaire would be suited by longer trips after having taken an extended
mile and a quarter race at York in August.
</TEXT>
