<DOCNO>GH950919-000050</DOCNO>
<DOCID>GH950919-000050</DOCID>
<DATE>950919</DATE>
<HEADLINE>Market for a winner</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>WHITE AND GOLD</BYLINE>
<EDITION>3</EDITION>
<PAGE>32</PAGE>
<RECORDNO>976306340</RECORDNO>
<TEXT>
EMERGING Market can earn further Epsom success this afternoon for dual
Derby-winning trainer John Dunlop.
He has shown useful form since stepping up to seven furlongs this
season and looks to have first-rate claims in the Ron Smyth Stakes.
Ocean Park is worth chancing against some exposed rivals in the
closing Ladbroke Handicap.
The four-year-old's comfortable win at Southwell in June on his first
start for Lady Herries marked him out as a gelding with improvement in
him and he goes well enough fresh.
Petit Point can underline trainer Richard Hannon's fine recent form by
taking the Dynasty maiden at Nottingham.
Trainer Peter Chapple-Hyam should land the opening race with Ailesbury
Hill, who takes a drop in class after having contested the May Hill
Stakes at Doncaster last time out.
</TEXT>
