<HEADLINE>Son rises at Hanson</HEADLINE>
<EDITION>3</EDITION>
<PAGE>27</PAGE>
<RECORDNO>976306348</RECORDNO>
<TEXT>
ROBERT Hanson, the 34-year-old son of Lord Hanson, is stepping up his
responsibilities at his father's industrial conglomerate following the
announcement that vice-chairman Martin Taylor is to retire at the end of
the month.
Mr Taylor, 61, has been vice-chairman since 1988. Christopher Collins,
the group's corporate development director, who has been deputising for
Mr Taylor for the past year, is due to take over his role.
Mr Hanson, who has been a main board director for three years and
worked under Mr Collins for five years, is to take over responsibility
for corporate development at Hanson in addition to his other duties.
</TEXT>
