<HEADLINE>Golf drive clinches #600,000 worth of US business</HEADLINE>
<EDITION>3</EDITION>
<PAGE>27</PAGE>
<RECORDNO>976306351</RECORDNO>
<TEXT>
A GROUP of 11 Scottish companies producing and selling specialist
items for golf clinched #600,000 of new business at the US Professional
Golf Association trade show in Las Vegas last week.
The companies, selling everything from tartan trousers to antique
clubs, exhibited at a stand organised by Scottish Trade International.
''It was an outstanding success. We got orders worth about #600,000,''
said Robert Thompson, whose Paisley-based firm Antique Golf was one of
the participants.
Mr Thompson said 23 Scottish golf companies belong to a recently
formed export group, Links of Scotland, which hopes to send an even
bigger delegation to the next US PGA conference in Orlando, Florida, in
January.
''The companies which were at the stand in Las Vegas all did extremely
well and they want to go again,'' he said.
Mr Thompson said that next time it was hoped to include Scottish
manufacturers of knitwear, waterproofs and glassware, who were missing
at the Las Vegas trade show.
His own firm sells golf clubs, balls and memorabilia dating from 1840
to 1920.
</TEXT>
