<HEADLINE>Estate agents more optimistic</HEADLINE>
<EDITION>3</EDITION>
<PAGE>25</PAGE>
<RECORDNO>976306352</RECORDNO>
<TEXT>
A GLIMMER of light in the gloomy housing market was reported today.
The Royal Institution of Chartered Surveyors' latest survey of members
practising as estate agents showed interest from potential buyers
exceeded expectations in August, which is traditionally a quiet month.
''This is encouraging because it could herald the beginning of an
increase in the number of transactions,'' said a spokesman.
''August turned out to be a better month in some ways than expected,
and interest rate reductions by mortgage lenders should help to boost
purchaser confidence over the coming few weeks -- albeit from a low
base.''
While a third of those questioned reported lower house prices in the
previous three months -- the worst figure for three years -- two-thirds
said prices had remained stable in their area.
</TEXT>
