<HEADLINE>Marks sparks at Festival show</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>ALISON KERR</BYLINE>
<EDITION>3</EDITION>
<PAGE>8</PAGE>
<ARTICLETYPE>FEATURE</ARTICLETYPE>
<GRAPHIC>ILLUS</GRAPHIC>
<RECORDNO>976306415</RECORDNO>
<TEXT>
* EDINBURGH'S multi-faceted Festival Theatre has been many things to
many people since its refurbishment and re-opening last year. One thing
it hasn't served as before, however, is a venue for a fashion show. All
that will change on Thursday as M&amp;S Live -- the Marks &amp; Spencer roadshow
-- rolls into town.
Edinburgh is the only Scottish city hosting the event, which is taking
place at another 18 venues across Britain. There will be two chances, at
6.30pm and 8.30pm, to catch the show which combines choreographed
catwalk, theatre and dance routines as performed by professional models
and dancers, and which spotlights the latest Marks &amp; Spencer collections
of womenswear, menswear and childrenswear. The newest range of home
furnishings will also be on display.
Tickets for the show are #6 each and can be acquired by calling
HomeChoice on 01925 667766 (payment by Account Card, Switch or Delta) or
directly from the customer service desk at Marks &amp; Spencer, Edinburgh. A
guaranteed #10,000 from ticket proceeds will go to the Western General
Hospital Trust Endowment Fund -- Cancer Caring Centre. On Thursday, the
Edinburgh store will stay open until 10pm to allow card customers, and
those attending the 6.30pm show, time to buy whatever caught their eye
during the performance.
</TEXT>
