<DOCID>GH950919-000149</DOCID>
<DATE>950919</DATE>
<HEADLINE>Vox crocks</HEADLINE>
<EDITION>3</EDITION>
<PAGE>6</PAGE>
<RECORDNO>976306439</RECORDNO>
<TEXT>
WINSTON-SALEM: The voices of rock and gospel artists have to work
harder even when they sing the same tune, an American study has found.
Choral and classical styles were easiest on the voice with bluegrass and
country music close seconds, but rock and gospel created most tension in
the throat, meaning most stress to the voice.
</TEXT>
