<EDITION>3</EDITION>
<PAGE>6</PAGE>
<RECORDNO>976306440</RECORDNO>
<TEXT>
TBILISI: Georgia's Deputy Security Minister and the chief aide of a
powerful warlord have been arrested and accused of masterminding last
month's car-bomb attempt to assassinate 67-year-old leader Eduard
Shevardnadze. Both are said to have confessed to the attack outside the
Parliament in the capital, Tbilisi.
</TEXT>
