<HEADLINE>Cuba ban attacked</HEADLINE>
<EDITION>3</EDITION>
<PAGE>6</PAGE>
<RECORDNO>976306445</RECORDNO>
<TEXT>
HAVANA: Moves in the US to extend the economic embargo against Cuba
were blinkered and could hamper efforts towards closer world trade
co-operation, said Ian Taylor, Minister for Science and Technology. On a
visit to the communist-ruled island, he said investment by British firms
in Cuba was growing.
