<HEADLINE>Trial delayed</HEADLINE>
<EDITION>3</EDITION>
<PAGE>6</PAGE>
<RECORDNO>976306446</RECORDNO>
<TEXT>
BANGKOK: The case against two Britons accused of drug smuggling in
Thailand was postponed again after a witness from an airline firm failed
to appear in court for the third time. Sandra Gregory, from Sowerby
Bridge, West Yorkshire, has admitted trafficking in 89g of heroin and
did not appear in court. Robert Lock, from Cambridge, denies the charge
and was remanded until October 27.
