<EDITION>3</EDITION>
<PAGE>3</PAGE>
<RECORDNO>976306476</RECORDNO>
<TEXT>
AN eight-year-old boy was ''serious but stable'' in hospital in
Edinburgh yesterday after a road accident on a visit to relatives in
Livingston on Sunday night. Daniel Barrie was rushed to the Royal
Hospital for Sick Children after he was hit by a van.
</TEXT>
