<DATE>950919</DATE>
<HEADLINE>Ban lifted</HEADLINE>
<EDITION>3</EDITION>
<PAGE>3</PAGE>
<RECORDNO>976306477</RECORDNO>
<TEXT>
A BUS company executive yesterday successfully persuaded an Inverness
sheriff to restore his driving licence because, he said, he couldn't
rely on public transport. Highland Scottish Omnibuses financial
controller Michael Beveridge, 29, had been banned for three years in
July, 1993, after his second drink-driving offence.
</TEXT>
