<DOCID>GH950919-000188</DOCID>
<DATE>950919</DATE>
<HEADLINE>Death in street</HEADLINE>
<EDITION>3</EDITION>
<PAGE>3</PAGE>
<RECORDNO>976306478</RECORDNO>
<TEXT>
A MAN who collapsed and died in Govan Road, Glasgow, yesterday was
named by police as Mr Daniel Heaney, 35, of Holmfauldhead Road, Govan.
Police said there were no suspicious circumstances and a report is being
prepared for the procurator-fiscal. One line of inquiry being pursued is
that the death may be drugs-related, which would make it the 78th in
Strathclyde this year.
</TEXT>
