<DOCID>GH950919-000189</DOCID>
<DATE>950919</DATE>
<HEADLINE>Culture award</HEADLINE>
<EDITION>3</EDITION>
<PAGE>3</PAGE>
<RECORDNO>976306479</RECORDNO>
<TEXT>
AUTHOR, broadcaster, and Scottish historian Billy Kay is this year's
winner of the Heritage Society of Scotland award for his contribution
towards reawakening Scottish culture. From a record 23 nominees, Mr Kay
polled more than half the votes. His award will be a specially
commissioned sculpture by David Annand.
</TEXT>
</DOC>
<DOC>
