<HEADLINE>Ten charged at demonstration</HEADLINE>
<EDITION>1</EDITION>
<PAGE>3</PAGE>
<RECORDNO>976306480</RECORDNO>
<TEXT>
TEN demonstrators were arrested yesterday following a protest at
Dundee's Ninewells Hospital by the Campaign Against Hospital Cuts and
Closures.
Demonstrator Philip Stott said: ''We are taking the anger of the
people of Dundee right to the doorstep of the unelected bureaucrats who
are destroying our NHS.'' A Tayside Police spokesman said: ''Ten people
have been charged following an incident.''
</TEXT>
