<HEADLINE>Hit-and-run driver fined</HEADLINE>
<EDITION>3</EDITION>
<PAGE>3</PAGE>
<RECORDNO>976306482</RECORDNO>
<TEXT>
A HIT-and-run driver who mounted the pavement and ploughed into three
men was fined #75 yesterday. At Dumbarton Sheriff Court Robert Jennings,
32, of Hall Street, Renton, Dunbartonshire, admitted careless driving
and failing to stop. He said he had panicked.
His pleas of not guilty to the more serious charge of dangerous
driving and one of assault were accepted by the Crown. Of the three
victims, one was treated for multiple fractures in Glasgow's Western
Infirmary.
</TEXT>
