<DOCNO>GH950919-000194</DOCNO>
<DOCID>GH950919-000194</DOCID>
<DATE>950919</DATE>
<HEADLINE>Royal cars in demand</HEADLINE>
<EDITION>3</EDITION>
<PAGE>3</PAGE>
<RECORDNO>976306484</RECORDNO>
<TEXT>
A 1994 AUDI 2.3-litre Cabriolet used by the Princess of Wales sold at
auction yesterday for #23,000 -- about #6000 more than its forecourt
value.
The emerald green car -- registration number L449 TRP -- with cream
leather interior, sports steering wheel, and multi-play CD stacker --
was loaned to Princess Diana last year and featured in hundreds of
photographs.
A 1981 Ford Escort, given to the princess by the Prince of Wales
before they were married, went for #4600 -- as much as it cost new.
The Audi was bought by an anonymous Singapore investment banker who
intends to keep the car at his London home close to the princess's
residence at Kensington Palace.
The princess has now bought a dark blue, 2.6-litre Audi.
</TEXT>
