<HEADLINE>New BBC presenter</HEADLINE>
<EDITION>3</EDITION>
<PAGE>3</PAGE>
<RECORDNO>976306487</RECORDNO>
<TEXT>
GRAMPIAN Television newscaster Anne Mackenzie is to join BBC Scotland,
it was confirmed yesterday.
She will present BBC radio's flagship news and current affairs
programme Good Morning Scotland and will also appear on televison
presenting Reporting Scotland one day a week.
Ms Mackenzie, 35, said: ''Good Morning Scotland is a programme I have
always wanted to work on.''
</TEXT>
